    <div class="grid-row">
      <div class="col-12">
        <h4>Molly lives at the campsite for the fifth time. She brings her son Sam who is allergic to rabit skin. Therefore she has filed a complaint about the plans to build a children's zoo.</h4>
        <h6>There can be many reasons for Molly's being unhappy about the new plans. You should for each reason select if this will make Molly annoyed or sad.</h6>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-row">
      <div class="col-12">
        <matchInteraction responseIdentifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="true" maxAssociations="0" minAssociations="0">
          <prompt/>
          <simpleMatchSet>
            <simpleAssociableChoice identifier="Annoyed" fixed="false" showHide="show" matchMax="0" matchMin="0">Annoyed</simpleAssociableChoice>
            <simpleAssociableChoice identifier="Sad" fixed="false" showHide="show" matchMax="0" matchMin="0">Sad</simpleAssociableChoice>
          </simpleMatchSet>
          <simpleMatchSet>
            <simpleAssociableChoice identifier="leftout" fixed="false" showHide="show" matchMax="1" matchMin="0">
              <div>Sam will feel left out because he cannot play with other children in the children's zoo.</div>
            </simpleAssociableChoice>
            <simpleAssociableChoice identifier="sneeze" fixed="false" showHide="show" matchMax="1" matchMin="0">The family will have to listen to Sam sneeze all the time.</simpleAssociableChoice>
            <simpleAssociableChoice identifier="bored" fixed="false" showHide="show" matchMax="1" matchMin="0">
              <div>Sam will be bored because he cannot play at the playground next to the children's zoo anylonger.</div>
            </simpleAssociableChoice>
            <simpleAssociableChoice identifier="money" fixed="false" showHide="show" matchMax="1" matchMin="0">
              <div>Molly will have to spend many money on allergy pills for Sam.</div>
            </simpleAssociableChoice>
            <simpleAssociableChoice identifier="involved" fixed="false" showHide="show" matchMax="1" matchMin="0">
              <div>Molly has been at the campsite for many years, and therefore she would like to be involved in the decisions.</div>
            </simpleAssociableChoice>
          </simpleMatchSet>
        </matchInteraction>
      </div>
